          <Comment>This variant is a gross deletion of the genomic region encompassing exon(s) 4-7 of the GBE1 gene. This deletion is out-of-frame, and is expected to create a premature termination codon and result in an absent or disrupted protein product. Loss-of-function variants in GBE1 are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 15452297, 20058079). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals affected with GBE1-related conditions. For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
